= System requirements

The system must satisfy the requirements for aero-acoustic MEMS microphones in wind tunnel tests and flight tests.

For the wind tunnel test in closed section, the required frequency range is from 100 Hz to 100 kHz. The dynamic range goes from 30 dB SPL up to 150 dB SPL for airframe noise, and up to 170 dB SPL for rotor and fan noise. The target SNR is 90 dB, and the temperature range is from -20 °C to 70 °C.

For the flight test application, the frequency range is from 40 Hz to 10 kHz. The dynamic range goes from 45 dB SPL up to 145 dB SPL for airframe noise, and up to 175 dB SPL for rotor and fan noise. The target SNR is 70 dB, and the temperature range is from -65 °C to 30 °C.

The selected MEMS sensors are dual-frequency sensors. They have two outputs: LF and HF. The LF output is used for the low-frequency band, and the HF output is used for the high-frequency band.

The Aeromic sensors have a target bandwidth from 100 Hz to 100 kHz, a dynamic range of 140 dB, and a sensitivity between 5 mV/Pa and 10 mV/Pa.

The final system must use 80 MEMS sensors. Since each sensor has two outputs, the system has to acquire 160 analog signals in total. The electronics must also be powered from a 28 V aircraft DC bus or from a 24 V auxiliary battery.